2026-04-13T18:52:16.296829Z  INFO ThreadId(04) ✅ [AI OUT] Generated Reply: The GHOSTDAG protocol uses the "chain of blocks" concept to prevent orphan blocks. It stores transactions in a chain of blocks, with each block containing a unique identifier and a hash of the previous block. If a transaction is not included in a block, it is considered orphan. To ensure the integrity of the blockchain, nodes verify the transactions at the end of each block. If a block contains transactions that have not been included, it is marked as orphan and cannot be included in the next block. This ensures that the network remains consistent and secure, allowing for the efficient transmission of data over the internet.
